\begin_layout Standard
The filter itself takes an image 
\begin_inset Formula $I$
\end_inset

 and outputs the result 
\begin_inset Formula $F$
\end_inset

: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray}
V_{1} & = & (I*k_{1}*k_{1}^{T})\label{eq:waveletV1}\\
V_{2} & = & (V_{1}*k_{2}*k_{2}^{T})\label{eq:waveletV2}\\
V_{3} & = & (V_{2}*k_{3}*k_{3}^{T})\label{eq:waveletV3}\\
F & = & \begin{cases}
V_{2}-V_{3} & \mathrm{{if\, user\, selected\, third\, plane\, option}}\\
V_{1}-V_{2} & \mathrm{{otherwise}}
\end{cases}\,.\label{eq:waveletF}
\end{eqnarray}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
All of the kernels above are vectors and are separable.
 We implemented the filter as written in equations (
